One person died and three others were injured, one critically and two seriously, when a bakkie and a car collided on the N7 near Malmesbury in the Western Cape on Saturday, paramedics said. Two more people were seriously injured in the collision at about 7.50am, ER24 spokesperson Annine Siddall said. At the time of their arrival ER24 paramedics found one patient trapped in the light motor vehicle and unfortunately did not manage to save the patient. The person was declared dead prior to extrication. A woman front passenger of a green bakkie was ejected with an isolated head injury and was in a critical condition. The patients were transported to Tygerberg Hospital [in Cape Town] for further medical care, Siddall said. African News Agency (ANA) For more news your way, follow The Citizen on Facebook and Twitter